snippet.textDisplay:
*TRANSLATION*
Top of the morning to you
I’m Irish - Irish the Hedgehog

I was going to meet up with my old friend Tails and Sonic when suddenly I thought “I really want some potatoes right now”

And so then I went down to station square and the I bump into Big and I say “How are you big guy!” and he says “how are you”

And I just say “have you any news, how are you doing”, “well I am fine”. And then he says “Sonic was just here but that fool was kept talking about nothing”

So then I thought of my old fellow and suddenly Big says “Get out of that garden” and I thought he might have gone crazy and maybe he is just very sick

But then with Big I’m thinking he not the smartest person around if you know what I mean and quiet frankly he has a massive mouth and some say he is the owner of the Giant’s Causeway

And so finally I meet up with Tails and he is very stressed and he is moving around everywhere and he is one of my mates, you know

But the Chipper’s is so far away and I still want my potatoes. But Tails is out of is mind but that’s life as they say

And the rest of the day to yourself
Happy Saint Patrick’s Day!

— Your Welcome not Irish people —

snippet.textDisplay:
Aight imma try and translate

“Good evening”

“I am named Irish, Irish the hedgehog”

“I was to reunite with my friends Tilly and Sonk, then, suddenly, it occurred to me “Well, I am craving for some potatoes”

“And so, I went to Station Square, and meet Big, and I say “Well, how are you with your large form” and he replied “Irish, how are you my friend?””

“And I go “Well how’s your day? Well mine was great” and he goes “Well Sonk was just her and the buffoon was bickering about some nonsense””

“And then, I thought of my old friend and suddenly, Big rudely says “ Stop gawking!” And I thought me may have become crazed and the he was just insane all along”

“And I realised that Big, was actually quite an idiot and that he has a large appetite and quite gigantic”

“And then I finally reunite with my friend Tilly, and he seems quite intense and unorganised, but he still is one of my friends”

“But then I realised how far the restaurant still was, and I still craved potatoes but Tilly seems quite frantic at the moment and you know, he’s probably fine”

“And have a good day”

“Happy St. Patrick’s Day”

Keep in mind this is the best I could do and if anybody spots a mistake or mistranslation, please point it out
